reviews.text:
Came here yesterday and both the food and service were excellent. I was with our two small kids and we got a spot behind a wall so they couldn't destroy the place which I was thankful for. The food was excellent and flavorful. The curry and paneer needed a little bit of salt but that was an easy fix. Highly recommended.

Service was great too.

Recently a friend hosted a lunch at Bombay Tandoor, my first time visiting and I was not disappointed. Great ambience. Food was delicious as you can see in my plate: spinach chat has to be the best. I loved every item that day and can’t wait to go back and try other items on the menu

PERFECT! Every Time. There are not enough good words in the dictionary to describe the food, service, staff, & atmosphere of this Gem. I have 3 favorite restaurants in my life and this is one of them. I bring work associates here and they all agree everytime with out question. Also they switch up the menu regularly. The flavor and spices will make your day/ weekend Extravagant and extraordinary. This place is Zen. I recommend this place and come at least weekly. My only complaint is open more! Lol

Bombay Tandoor is providing a great service and a great taste. Their buffet were good. Buffet items was tasty and fresh. I liked chicken karhai, and channe more. Gulab Jaman were good among the desserts.
Overall, a good place for family and friends to visit.

Celebrated Christmas Day lunch with 11 family members. Great food and service. We ordered lamb chops and shrimp from a la carte. Laxman was awesome. They are in a hurry to clear plates so make sure if you are taking pictures or chatting they don’t take away expensive a la carte items or cutlery. Coming for years here and met Mr. and Mrs. Varma

I have always enjoyed eating at Panera Bread; I love this chain and highly recommend it. Almost every location I went to was spacious, had enough seating and tables, clean bathrooms, tidy and polished food-handlers, reasonable prices, fresh bakery, high quality salads, sandwiches, coffee and generous portions.
Panera is a great spot for getting either healthy food or downright bread. Very relaxed atmosphere and good food. Service is always good and food is always delivered fast.

This location is pretty big with both indoor and outdoor seating. I had to get my car serviced and needed to kill sometime so came here. Very clean, very friendly and helpful staff. If you haven’t really had this egg white spinach sandwich yet, you are missing out on deliciousness.

This was a good restaurant, but lately they are not doing a good gob, I ordered this morning 2 greek yogurt parfait and both of them were really messy they were sticky from outside because they put a lot of honey in there, I could say that there was more honey than yogurt on it, I had to trhow it away because I was in my way to work, it was really a bad experience, the las time was almost the same I ordered a yogurt parfait and they gave me just the yogurt with no fruit no granola in it, how am i supose to eat just the yogurt? And I payed almost $5 for it.  I have to mention that all my orders were online for pick it up.

We enjoyed using our Panera Bread gift cards this morning.  This restaurant location was about one mile from our lodging, so it was very convenient to find it.  The order taker was very friendly.  They were out of my preference, my second menu choice tasted great!  It’s good that social distancing and mask wearing are practiced here!

Bustling crowded place but they won't turn you away. We still got seated immediately. The food came quickly and the portions were huge as well as not expensive at all. The service was fast, nice and explained when necessary. Tried several dishes and things to go. Extra sauces, condiments, drinks, no problem.
This place serves no alcohol but lots of traditional food and drink.

My in-laws have been coming here since they originally opened and I got introduced to it 12 years ago after getting married. I have to tell you that they have been consistently good and serving excellent food and service. We ordered spinach dish and eggplants appetizer which was not on the menu and it was delicious as always. Highly recommend for anyone wanting to try simple delicious Persian food

They have a really nice welcome with fresh breads. There is nothing better than Kashke badenjan, which is so delectable that I could not stop eating it. Regarding the main food, the lamb shank and dill rice were good, but the shishlik kababs were not a complete portion, as we expected six pieces. We liked how juicy and well-cooked Soltani was. Various dining options are available, both outdoor and indoor, along with very good service. From what I've seen, they have a diverse menu at a reasonable price

Ask anyone that knows exceptional food, where to get the most authentic Persian food and they will say, Shamshiry! The bread is so fresh and served with butter & olive oil for dipping. I ordered a side of yogurt garlic sauce and Chelo Kabob kubideh with saffron rice, stew tomato & fresh onion slices!. I also ordered a fresh pot of Persian tea. You know when the place is full of Iranians, it has to be special. All of the kabobs are good and you can get lamb, chicken, beef or fish. The desserts are lovely and I’d especially recommend the Persian saffron ice cream.

The food was very good, however,  they served way too much rice.  This was done to compensate for the small cuts of lamb kabob.  The rice took up half the plate.  The meat was tasty but a bit over cooked.  The service was only good.  We no longer sat down and the server came and asked us if we were ready to order.  The atmosphere is sterile.  Not really conducive to relaxed dining.  The Persian Ice cream was excellent.  All in all a good place to go.

I was super excited to check this place out as I heard very good things about this place from several people! I wanted to give it a chance despite the bad reviews……
Unfortunately, the reviews people have left are not wrong.

GREAT VENUE & GREAT DANCING MUSIC however:

1. Drinks & hookah are overpriced! My friend asked for a cup of water and they refused her. She needed to purchase a $6 water bottle- that’s ridiculous!

2. The security guards are extremely rude! My friend got kicked out and they would not let her know why. They grabbed her by the arm being super aggressive, as if she was a big threat. NO NEED! I kindly and politely asked them what was the reason. They didn’t even acknowledge that I was speaking to them. I repeated myself a few times and finally he says “step outside and we can talk”
We finally get outside and they still didn’t want to tell us the reason and told us to have a good night. I was extremely upset at that point!

Unfortunately, it’s a place that now I’m skeptical about recommending or even consider going back.

Will start with the pros, music, ambiance, lights, dancing!
Cons is pretty much everything else, outrageous prices for water ($6 bottle), alcohol ($15 shots).
Had an issue with security that wouldn't let me in at first since my shoes were not "Yeezys" I kid you not. Manager had to come and let them know I was dressed well. If you are a woman, this is a great spot, as a guy maybe think twice.

I have frequented this place both in Arlington and Tysons. I pay the 20$ cover (higher for special events), tip the coat check, tip the bathroom person, tip the bartenders, always buy food and expensive drinks for me and whoever I am with, and pay to reserve tables. I have never dealt with consistently aggressive management at an establishment. I have seen maybe a rude cashier or a rude server here or there at other places but management? Wow. Especially aggressive to a frequent customer who spends lots of money there every time he goes and is friendly with everyone. Afraid to go back. The recent issue (not the first), I reserve a table they try to take the table later in the night and I have to show a receipt for the table to save the table I paid money for. Problem solved. Few weeks later SAME situation happens only instead, I show the receipt and this time the manager says I am having an attitude by telling him I reserved the table and by showing him the receipt. Kicks me off the table I paid for and threatens to kick me out for showing him my receipt. No apology, no other table given. Calls me respectfully explaining I paid for the table and showing my receipt proving I purchased the table "attitude" and threatens to kick me out.  I just respectfully closed my tab, tipped coat check, tipped the awesome bartender, shook hands, gave hugs and left of my own accord. Management has a known history for being too eager to kick people out so I didn't want to risk staying another minute. There are too many Latin dance establishments in the area for me to risk having another bad night at this one.

I went to the Salsa Club on a Friday and it was a great experience. I got tickets off Eventbrite it was free entry before 11pm. It was a group of 4. When we got in the door and checked in we were offered a table for $40 which was a great price.

Once we got in the set up was very airy and they had a very good set up of tables and couches. One thing I liked was at the tables they had electronic menus as well. Once we got our drinks the general manager Damien actually came by and offered us a bigger seating arrangement with no extra charge. Which we greatly appreciated and it was just great customer service after the night we had prior to coming there.

The staff was friendly and the people there were great. Everyone just wanted to have a good time everyone was smiling it was just great to be out. The music was great as well. I went to the salsa club when you were located in arlington and I like this set up better.

I will definitely be back! Thank you for a great experience.

Used to be a regular since they were in Arlington but ever since they moved to Tysons the place has been going downhill. The cover and drinks are ridiculously expensive and not worth the price. The music lately has been really boring (how is it that they advertise bachata night but play like 80% salsa?). There are more affordable/nicer options in DC and I can see this place going out of business soon if they don't do something to keep people coming back. They started charging $20 cover during the pandemic but once they had a taste for it they never went back to charging reasonable prices if anything at all.

name: Sakura Japanese Steak, Seafood House & Sushi Bar

reviews.text: Sakura delivers excellence every time. We came here before a concert and it hit the spot. I ordered the chicken hibachi with mushroom appetizer which also comes with soup and salad. The soup is basically a chicken broth with a few mushrooms. The salad has a ginger dressing and is very good. If you order a hibachi entree you also get a choice of appetizer like mushrooms, shrimp, or chicken livers. They also offer sushi made to order. If you do not want to sit at a hibachi seat as they have a separate dining area if your prefer. The portions are very large and cooked to perfection. There is ample parking directly out front and is right off route 7.

Great hibachi restaurant . I usually do take out but I actually ate in for the 1st time during lunch and it was even better than take out. Our cook was great and his name was “ Taco Bell” I found that pretty funny. I honestly have no complaints. I do recommend giving this spot a try 👍🏼

First full experience with hibachi style and honestly have to say, wasn’t really a big fan.  I can see how it might be entertaining but you literally sit right by the blazing hot grill, and the chef takes forever to cook the veggies, then fried rice and then the meats.  But the time your meats/seafood are done, the rest of your food is cold—I got the Ribeye steak and Chicken—the steak was fairly quick but the chicken took a while and was last to finish cooking.

Also, I felt that our chef did not respect the customers when some of us said we didn’t want shrimp thrown at us (to catch in our mouth) and he kept being aggressive about it and ended up missing a few times per person too.

We came here to celebrate the birthday of a friend.  Most of the food is prepared in front of you, items are stir fried and served. The performance of cooking is a big part of the experience. Some of us were vegetarian and others were not, so server cooked the vegetarian items first, so meat eaters had to wait a bit.

If you are a smaller group, there will be others sitting at your table, or you might have to join a larger group.

Had dinner here, great hibachi. Teriyaki chicken is outstanding. Very attentive service, loved it. Chef’s are good and keeping the place lively . Kids menu is not so great, but they will enjoy the entertainment by the chefs during their cooking. Price is reasonable. Will visit again soon!

Amazing experience. Went for our anniversary and everything was spot on. Rather loud seat neighbors, but they were tuned out.

Was seated fast as we had reservations. Celebratory tinsel sprinkled on the table. Excellent waitress. Food was great. Ordered my first tomahawk steak, wife had surf and turf also had crab stuffed mushrooms, & lobster Mac and cheese.

Thank you for the wonderful experience.

A first. Husband's Birthday and he had always wanted to try Ruth's Chris Steakhouse. We arrived a little early, hut the professionalism of the staff was welcomingly and friendly. 5 stars for staff. A little disappointed on selection of Beer but blown away with the food. Starters Chop Salad, and Stuffed Mushrooms. Very good salad, balanced and well dressed. The mushroom were outstanding, flavor was spot on. As it was Husband's Birthday je chose Tomahawk Steak, as always rare, blue rare very appreciative, cream spinach, and Brussels sprouts. The Tomahawk per husband was perfect, and it a description he has never used elsewhere. Which is saying something from this SD man who grew up on beef. The cream spinach in his words was a spasm of joy. As for the Brussels sprouts he asked I remember the flavor to copy at home. As this was Husband's night will leave review on his experience. Highly recommend and enjoyed the atmosphere, food and staff. Thank you Staff.

The service was perfect from the host to our servers and even the manager stopping by to check on us. The food was delicious, au gratin potatoes were perfect so cheesy and well seasoned and the steaks of course were very much worth it. Great experience overall .

We decided to have Thanksgiving dinner out for the first time. Ruth's was surprisingly very busy for the holiday. So make a reservation weeks in advance.
The food was delicious, although my house salad had way too much dressing on it. Will get dressing on the side next time.
Since I ordered the fillet oscar style the crabcake was on top and thus got cold. If it had been directly on the plate it would have been hot.
Overall we had a good time for the holiday. I'm glad they were open to accommodate.

We had a birthday dinner here and the food was delicious.  The host staff and wait staff were all attentive and made sure we had everything we needed, so much that we never even ran out of water.  We had the calamari, artichoke dip, ribeye, and stuffed chicken breast and everything was cooked perfectly.  My only complaint was that the stuffing on the chicken was a little too much butter and not much else and the bacon in our brussel sprouts side was too sweet.

What’s the point of calling in an order if it’s not going to be ready when you get there? I gave more than enough time for the pizza to be prepped, I come just to wait another 20 minutes. It was like they were just starting the order when I got there. Worst papa johns I’ve honestly ever encountered.

Every low google review is for a reason. Looking over domino branches generally in google, you would find an average rate of 3 star. Frankly speaking that is really poor, the rates normally reflect the service and quality.

Our experience: it takes around 3 minutes to our place, they charged 3 dollars for delivery which is really a joke, we are more than happy to tip the drivers. The pizza came after more than one hour and considering the distance and how hot pizza got here, we can clearly see the delay was caused because of the kitchen.

Hope you can receive these feedback and try to improve service quality.  These reviews would result in losing customers. Happy customers are less likely to leave a review.

If only they posted that they pay minimum wage and expect every one to drive, no union, harassment at all levels and they will steal ur wages when they claim u fire yourself for asking about the aforementioned fallacies.  Plus they pay a lawyer to repress these truths, and the judge,... if take off wasn't shot here I wouldn't have posted this either...

If I could give a 0 star I would. I have never written a review for anything, but this Papa John is something special.
After 2 and half hours of waiting for a delivery, the pizza arrived cold and all the slices ran into each other or top of one another, like it was thrown around.
This is not the first time this has happened and we had to deal with a rude employee that calls herself the manager.
Horrible service.

I was honestly a bit skeptical ordering from here due to the negative reviews, but I was pretty hungry and in a rush. I ordered a small pepperoni pizza, 8pc wings, a papadia and some garlic knots. I didn't wait to long. Everything was great and the food was very hot. I would definitely go there again 👌.

FAMILY FRIENDLY!!!  Patrick and his team were really amazing!  Haven't experienced such incredible hospitality like that in a long time.  Very clean and organized, hospitable, patient, efficient and extremely generous.  Not to mention, awesome sale on pizza that was absolutely delicious!  Highly recommend!!

Since I discovered this gem of a restaurant, I eat at one of their locations weekly. I am even a part of their loyalty program. I'm Italian so I'm really picky when it comes to my pizza. Paisano's has the BEST pizza I've had in a very long time!! Plus, the employees are nice and make you feel at home. I highly recommend this place!! Ignore any negative reviews. We ALL make mistakes. Don't judge a place by one experience. You never know what someone else is going through. Be kind.

This place is so clean and the staff are very friendly. I ordered a medium cheese with extra cheese cut into squares to eat with my kids. The staff brought the food to my table with all the utensils and plates and were so kind. The pizza was perfect.
It was the worse pizza I ever had . I got 16” Supreme it literally didnt have any cheese . it looks like it was left unattended in the oven for a long time 😞 .

The staff and service we received were excellent. So friendly, professional and precise.
I ordered steak and cheese w/ fries which as very good. Will definitely come again

Clean and well kept, with attentive service. Tends to be much less busy than the nearby Pike 7 Plaza location (next to the Greensboro Metro Station)--roughly 40% less foot traffic. No complaints except the early closing hours on Sunday (1pm).

Nice and welcoming Starbucks. They make an amazing iced caramel macchiato, the way it’s supposed to be made!

The staff is nice and attentive. The place is clean and they have nice music playing too.

Easy to find and conveniently located

Ok. The Baristas are very nice. The parking is easy. The bathrooms are DISGUSTING. I mean I literally had to clean to toilet seat. Look at the sink!!! Makes you nervous to eat here. Look at the buildup around the sink and in the toilet.

The chicken Sausage and Bacon Biscuit is amazing. Staff is friendly and quick. The store is clean and comfortable with a good sense of organization. Close to plenty of other stores, I stopped by while getting an oil change. You should also expect the usual menu options and enjoy like other Starbucks.
Staff and service here is wonderful. My dog loves to come in for pup cups and the staff is Always very welcoming and personable.

I would give them a quarter star.  A big fat -0 if I could . Awful awful service! My co worker picked up orders for us and my Coffee was ice cold and as you can see there was no extra vanilla foam and coffee is bitter. I’ve tried to give them chance after chance and have been disappointed every time. Whenever I order the strawberry refresher or the pineapple refresher it taste like water with just a splash of fruit. Muffins was stale old and dry. Today was my final straw and so I will never ever ever order from this store again. I’ve been calling for the past 30 minutes to let them no and no one has bothered to answer the phone. Run don’t walk away from this store!!!! Awful awful awful service!!!!!!🤬😡🤬😡🤬

Its a beautiful store. The employees were friendly and no one was in the store it was pretty empty but they didn’t fill my cup properly and I ordered a venti. The cup was filled like they put a grande in a venti cup. However they actually have merch in stock and i found a cup ive been wanting do that was the only decent part

Out if hot breakfast items for days.  Staff and managers don't know why or when it will be resolved. This isn't unique to this store so the store manager should have a better idea
Asked fir the Regional manager number and was told that I can call corporate
There are cheaper options out there to consider
Great atmosphere, helpful staff and tasty pikes place coffee! Tea prices a bit high considering other options......(it's just a cup of water and a tea bag!)......
Great atmosphere, friendly staff, delicious pastries and the best coffee.

We had an event at the office and contacted Boulevard.  We gave them a budget and they suggested several menus for us to select from.  They were quick to respond to our inquiries and responsive to our questions.  We chose a Mediterranean menu.  Our food arrived on time, including utensils/plates/napkins which I had forgotten to request.  The food not only tasted wonderful but it looked good on the platters and had been carefully plated and prepared.  Everyone enjoyed it and several attendees even requested the name of the caterer for their own events.  We will be calling them back again for future events.  Thank you very much.

The food and service are incredible! Everyone at my wedding could not stop raving about how delicious the food was! Everyone on the team is so easy to work with. I couldn't have asked for a better catering company to do my wedding.
Excellent sandwiches and at a reasonable price as well. I’ve been there about six times as the café is in the building I work in. Every sandwich I have had has been top-notch. Well worth it.
This rating is for the old owner of this cafe! We miss the warm family vibes. Sweetie ppl in the world.
I had the taco special since I just moved into the area. They were pretty good but didn't fill me up.

name: Potbelly
vicinity: 1577 Spring Hill Road Ste 100 Ste 100, Tysons

reviews.text: One of my favorite sandwhich places. Great location and friendly staff as well. I love these sandwhiches and they are delicious and made with fresh, high quality ingredients. The hot peppers here are the BEST, and you can buy them in jars to take home. They are quick here and this is a great place to grab lunch in Tysons. Also any time I have had an issue at this location they resolved it right away. Great sandwhiches and company.
Ordered via online for pick up. Inside was clean and my food was waiting on the pick up shelf. I requested my drink and was promptly tended to.

Potbelly is my favorite sandwich shop. I always order the chicken and cheddar on white with bacon mayo and lettuce. The service is fast, and the employees are kind. I’m also a fan of the broccoli cheddar soup, but today I’m trying the chicken pot pie soup. Good drink selection. They also have tasty desserts like cookies and brownies. A bit pricey, but way better than Subway or Quiznos.

Briefly stopped by today to get some ice cream. I was surprised to taste their vanilla ice cream which was full of flavor. Friendliest people ever. Clean shop with large parking. Outdoor seating is nice and plenty. Will come again!!

I’ve gotten sandwiches from this location a handful of times and never had any complaints. Today I ordered online for pickup , which included a milk shake. I lost track of time and was 15 minutes late getting my food and figured the shake would be melted. But they were nice enough to keep it in a cooler so it was still perfect when I got it. And it was delicious!

Went there after reading all the gold star ratings. Wasn’t busy as it was a weekday night. First thing I noticed was the sticky floors. Secondly the person who created our box was not wearing any gloves and picked the chicken with his beer hands. Also saw another staff members wiping her hands off her jeans even though she had an apron on. That is unhgenic!

The chicken however tasted great. Instant aroma of charcoal chicken. It was moist. Good serving. Good coleslaw and fried rice as a side.

Our favorite Peruvian roasted chicken (pollo a la brasa) place in the US! The roasted chicken is very flavorful, and the portion is also very large. For the sides, their fries and yuca are both processed in Peruvian way, not the French fries in normal American restaurants. Definitely try the spicy green sauce with the yuca fries! On weekends, they also serves ceviche, which is also fresh and delicious. Highly recommend to people who like Peruvian food!

The chicken flavor is great, generous amounts and variety of sides. The only concern is that the order’s container goes back and forward from the kitchen to the customer and then customer back to the kitchen which is not sanitary at all.

Hellooooooooo!!! Today we will talk about   "super chicken" this is charcoal chicken is located in Tysons corner i only have to say is the most delicious charcoal chicken i eat ever  if you have time to go don't doubt just do it and enjoy this delicious chicken charcoal!!  They have restrooms 🚻  plany parking and is complete cleaning restaurant !! I recommend this highly 300% !! Good luck

Chicken was good. Sides were not very appetizing.
Great value for money.
Good People, Good Food, Clean and Best Prices in town. Just looking for quick lunch this is the place.  Main lobby take Elevator to LL.

Great food at very reasonable prices. Had a steak and cheese with fries, and they really hit the spot.

It's a little difficult to find because there's no signage. It's in the LL of the building, so how on the elevator and go down a floor to get there
Interesting wide ranging menu for a small deli. Everything tastes good and fresh. So i give this deli a lot of credit! Try their burger- its only like $5.50.

Place is a little hard to find it’s in the lower level (“LL”on elevator then follow the signs that say “Deli”) of an office building but it’s well worth the walk food is good, prices are fair and the customer service is very friendly. Ill definitely stop by when im in the area. I had a Sausage, Bacon Egg and Cheese on a croissant. Definitely a Deli feel too it. A bit small of a location but definitely great overall.

Good convenient food if you work in the building. Only one piece of advice to management, there should be a staff member completely dedicated to the cash register. This would improve the customer experience immensely.
Missing orders and super slow, I ordered two burger only came out one. Also, they seems never clean this place, it’s dirty everywhere.

Saw a commercial last night for breakfast. Figured I'd try it. Decided to try the maple chicken bacon sandwich instead of an egg sandwich.  Big mistake. A fried piece of ... something ... doused in syrup. Yuk. Never again.
The only reason I gave 2 stars is because the sandwich was temperature hot, as requested.
Cashier was very friendly.

This was officially the slowest fast food I have ever eaten. Nobody was at the register for the majority of the time we were in the restaurant and the staff was both unresponsive and unfriendly. They appeared to have forgotten the order (within 2 min of it being placed). Do not go here

It seems like this Wendy's is only good for drive thru.....inside was atrocious..sticky floors that appear to have never been cleaned all day...soda machine not operational...the heavy smell of weed....rest room had someone washing in the sink....someone also had thrown up in the urinal....all I can say is that this was the first and last time for me in your establishment

Worst Wendy’s to go to. I went on Friday July 19th at 2:21pm. I had a Mobil order and the guy told me at the window he didn’t have it I have to come inside to look for my order I said can you please check. I only ordered a Mobil order because I was on lunch and trying to rush back to enjoy my food. I said well I have a Mobil order he argued with me about it not being there and he can’t move his spot to go check. WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE EVER. THE GUY WHO WORKED THE WINDOW NEEDS TO BE IN THE BACK COOKING OR CLEANING. I had to walk inside and find my order a lucky the nice guy who worked the front said it was a Mobil order and I’m sorry you had to get out the car. That was the only thing that made it better. The window guy does not ever need to work the window.

I won’t comment on whether McDonald is good for or not but I can confirm that this location continues to maintain the quality and speed of food which is consistent across what you see at McDonald’s nationwide. I’ve tried pick up as well as delivery through Uber eats and McDonald’s continues to remain McDonald’s.

Every single time we use the app for a mobile order, they neglect to fulfill the entire order. Tonight was no different. One worker argued with me about the 2 medium fries I ordered but weren't given. Even though it literally says 2 medium fries on the receipt that was stapled to the bag she initially handed me.
24 hours but i went there and they said they were closed on 23 jan, 2023 @ 230 am. If youre going to be closed then please update your times, otherwise dont lie to me at the drive thru.
Standard McDonald's.  Bathroom facilities were clean and well kept.  Offer touch screen ordering in the lobby or in-person.  Service was quick and no real complaints.
I ordered french fry and found a ROACH in the french fry. Please clean the restaurant and do pest for safe . It was terrible experience. We were almost done and it's very disgusting.

Hidden treasure in Vienna. ❤️❤️❤️ Tyco road is very tricky . Make sure run the google maps or
order delivery. Great food .Great staff.
Shahrad
Never disappointed by the fast service and quality dishes. Their handmade dumplings are out of this world delicious!
Hard to find take out place that had amazing food.  Not greasy and super flavorful. The Singapore noodles had just the right amount of kick.
Carry out only. Non-msg, cooked to order. Friendly service.  My favorite place for egg foo young and chicken wings. Hidden away in back of the complex.

A hidden gem in Tyson's Corner! I frequent this place and I am always satisfied with the quality of food. Wendy and crew work hard to make consistent orders and great tasting food! A must try for take out!

Unbelievably good. Infinitely better than chipotle. We always liked DT but haven’t been back in awhile but tried it again yesterday. The burrito was packed with flavor and we loved the touch screen menu so you can order exactly what you want.

District Taco is one of my favorite chains for Mexican/Latin cuisine. My go to is the beyond meat (Itza) tacos Mexican way along with an order of chips and guacamole.

I stopped by this chic strip mall for takeout since I was driving through the area and Google maps had them nearby.

On another note, the great thing about District Taco, as a whole, is they are open for breakfast, lunch, and dinner, which is a competitive advantage against other chains. What else is top-notch is the queso dip and the components to create your meal are almost farm fresh.

District Taco really got things right with it's "way" of doing business and you should give this place a shot if you get a little tingle in your belly.

Honestly I was expecting a bit more at this restaurant. The flavors were mostly lacking, and the meat was somewhat dry. When you eat tacos, at a taco stand especially, you are expecting to eat something made with love and care. This place has nice employees but you don't get that feeling as much here as you would at a more authentic taco spot. The corn tortillas were especially bland and overly salty, and getting it "Mexican style" didn't help it out. The fish tacos were even worse, as it was just soft fish with no crunch. Frying that fish up would have made this spot about 10 times better. If you do want to eat here however,  I would recommend going "Jeff style" but then you risk losing the flavor of the meat to the abundance of toppings. Overall it wasn't terrible but could be a lot better. The salsa was probably the best and most flavorful thing on the menu as well.

A little loud (echo-y) for my 1 year old but I was more worried for other patrons if she shrieked rather than her comfort. Employees were sweet, and food was ready quickly. Everything was tasty. Glad we stopped here even though we had not planned it out ahead of time.

It was very very good.  I happen to come in at the peak of lunch and it took a while to get my order. Update: 2 years from my last review. It is clearly a different world.  Only two customers in the entire place (three employees).  Still good food.  Picked up some tacos this time.

I used to eat here allot when it first opened, recently stopped by and ordered the Monday special which is suppose to be rice with ground beef. I literally had old soggy bland rice with little pieces of beef the size of a finger nail. I was so disappointed I told the guy about it and he took it back there and the ladies in the back just shrugged and sprinkled more rice with her gloves.

Nice people... just ok food. I've been twice now to confirm...  I think I will go elsewhere from now on.  They are decent kabobs if you happen to be in that plaza and want kebabs, although the are a few other good options for other cuisine there.

Food was excellent and service was even better. We tried several different things as I was trying to get my daughter to try something new. The staff threw in a few extras for her and she loved everything (she can be picky)!

Moby Moby Moby. It is as old as I remember. Met the founder a few times. His vision proved to be true. Great tasting food, decent price, and always the same quality and taste no matter when you re-visit. Daily specials are great but the chicken and lamb kabob is mouth watering.  With several locations around town it is hard to not run into one. A must try!!!

Moby did I is one of our favorite fast kabob places. It’s delicious fresh and reasonable prices. Totally recommend this location! The staff is nice and the place is clean. Really happy with our lunch :) our favorite was chicken chunks, the spicy chicken kabob. Can’t wait till next time to try their lamb chunks!

I held a two-day planning session for my team which included working lunches; a colleague recommended Kimberly's and it was excellent. We did the cold sandwich boxed lunches the first day and one of their "office get together" selections for the second (these are more like a selection of small bites and appetizers). Everything was on time, tasted great, and received a lot of compliments. This is my new go-to when I have similar events in the future.

I placed an order with Kimberly's for a work retirement luncheon that took place yesterday. Everything was perfect. The delivery and set-up were awesome. The food was absolutely amazing. Lastly, the customer service from Kimberly's is unmatched. Professional, friendly, and very accommodating. Highly recommended!

Kimberly's Catering did an excellent job catering a memorial service for my family.  The service and food they serve is a cut above.  They are organized, easy to deal with, and the food is delicious.  I have relied  on many different caterers for many different personal and professional functions, but rarely has the food been so well received!  I love their website, their service, their attention to detail, and their food.  Use them.  You won't regret it.  A+ on all criteria.

Our church has used Kimberly's Catering for its annual community outreach auction dinner for at least the past six years.  They are incredibly reliable in getting the food to us on time.  The food is always delicious.  There are many menu possibilities.  This dinner is very important to us  because it puts our bidders in an expansive and generous mood, and we can raise more money to give to local and international charitable organizations.  They have also catered holiday dinners for special occasions, and some informal lunches, for us.  Every time we have Kimberly's here, people rave about the food.  And they are easy to work with!  We love them.
I think I have carried Kimberly's Corporate Catering with me for 10 maybe 15 years.  They are my go to for catering needs.  They have always had wonderful service and wonderful food!
